history.content:
Please see my response in @2378. Let me know if you have more questions about the policy.

If you need help picking an alternative class, please contact Elad Alon at elad@berkeley.edu.

I'm a senior graduating in May. I am currently #21 on the waitlist for Spring 2017 EE16A. If I stay on the waitlist, what are my chances of getting in? I'd like to take 16A if at all possible or as a last resort, take an alternative that is lower div/comparable in difficulty. I'm not very strong in physics/pure math/mechE and EE16A is my last requirement to graduate, so I don't want to risk taking a course that's too difficult for me and being unable to pass. How will the EE16A waitlist policy impact my probability of getting into the class if I stay on the waitlist? Thanks!
history.subject: EE16A Waitlist for Seniors
